oc:kn_617a7025 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting cross-platform brand material discovery" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Start with Notion AI Search (broadest coverage via federation) 2. Follow up with Confluence for enterprise documentation 3. Check Google Drive for official brand documents 4. Check Box for cloud-stored brand documents 5. Search SharePoint/OneDrive for enterprise files 6. Search Slack for brand discussions and decisions 7. Search Gong for conversational brand patterns 8. Search Granola for meeting transcripts and notes 9. Review Figma for design-embedded brand guidelines" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ordered by breadth of coverage and likelihood of finding authoritative brand content" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_68330f56 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating Slack search results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Slack is a CONVERSATIONAL tier source — it should not be treated as authoritative for brand guidelines. Use it for context on brand evolution and informal decisions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Conversational sources capture informal brand discussions but lack the formality of official guidelines" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_9588e8a9 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When constructing search queries on any platform" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Core brand search queries: \"brand guidelines\", \"style guide\", \"brand voice\", \"tone of voice\", \"messaging framework\", \"value proposition\", \"competitive positioning\", \"brand standards\", \"brand kit\", \"design tokens\"" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These terms consistently surface brand-related content across all enterprise platforms" .

oc:kn_97ab4249 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a platform search yields no brand-related results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a platform returns zero results, try broader queries like 'marketing' or 'sales'. If still empty, check whether the platform is connected and authenticated, and note the gap in the discovery report." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Absence of content on a platform is itself useful diagnostic information" .

oc:kn_9c7ad5a0 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating recency of search results across all platforms" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Focus on content from the last 12 months for operational, conversational, and contextual sources. Only search further back for explicit brand documents like style guides and brand books." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Brand positioning evolves; older content from non-authoritative sources may reflect outdated positioning" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_aaf5ad6e a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When results from multiple platforms overlap" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Track source URLs to detect the same document across platforms. When duplicate content appears, prefer the most recently updated version." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Duplicate documents across platforms create confusion about which is authoritative; recency is the best disambiguator" .

oc:kn_ad193b8a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When searching Gong for conversational brand patterns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "In Gong, focus on closed-won calls from top performers to extract the brand voice that actually works in practice. Compare with average performers to identify consistent patterns." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Successful sales calls represent the brand voice in its most effective real-world application" .

oc:kn_b5bed30d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When Notion AI Search returns results from connected sources like Google Drive or SharePoint" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never double-search a platform when Notion federation already returned results from it" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Notion federates across connected sources, so results from other platforms appear in Notion search results" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_bb8a1b6c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before initiating any platform search" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Platform must be connected and authenticated before searching. Notion AI Search must have federation enabled to cover connected sources like Google Drive, SharePoint, OneDrive, Slack, Jira, Teams." .

oc:kn_edebe09a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When searching Confluence spaces for brand documentation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "On Confluence, look for pages with many watchers and recently updated brand root pages with hierarchical children. Check for PDF brand guides uploaded as attachments." ;
    oc:hasRationale "High watcher counts indicate important shared content; brand guidelines evolve and the latest versions are most relevant" .

